<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Hahaha, No Shmordon this is not your 'bad' half gordon, just someone that bought EQ when he had a VERY slow computer and was FORCED to travel and find less crowded zones/spots to hunt due to LAG restrictions! <P>Actually it was the BEST thing to happen to me, looking back on it (I STILL do not miss the 3-5min zone times I had to endure!). I had never even HEARD of a campable spawn until I reached level 39 with my mage! I found plenty of out of the way places to find plenty of free roaming experience.  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/biggrin.gif"><BR>A few examples:<P>The aviak village in SK (not the penthouse), where it works AGAINST you to camp the spawn sites! There you have to keep an eye on up to 7 different spawn sites to get a mob suitable for your level. <P>NK I do not know of a campable mob there, almost all of the spawns are random. Even the unique ones.<P>'Wisp isle' (Now this one MAY have changed since I played), good plat and wisp spawn that were regular (but they DID spawn at certain spots so they may be camped in this day and age).<P>Everfrost, wandering mamonths, ice bones, ice goblins, etc.<P>Seafury Isle, there are sooo many SF there that you are never in want of a target.  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/biggrin.gif"><P>I will not even get into DUNGEONS that do not lend themselves to camping. So, yes, you CAN get a LOT of experience and never camp a thing (got my mage up to lvl 52 this way, although he is in retriement now, due to Verant's current approach to the class)
