Future mage, the mage IS a good class. I LOVED my mage (still do) since its first day. BUT Verant seems to have NO IDEA of what the class should be like! Or worse, because they INVENTED the class, feel that they KNOW EXACTLY what it is like and how it should be played. Soooo all of our 'upgrades'(HA!) come pre-nerfed! Take the much harolded 'Rod of Modulation'. Verant was tired of mages complaining about 'escape spells' (other than gate we have NO protection if something goes wrong), so they came up with a ONE spell rod for storing mana. It cost almost as much mana to make as to use, PLUS it drains health! It is absolutely worthless. Verant claimed it would be highly sought after for grouping (sort of a mini manastone). It is STILL a laugh! Another instance: Mages are defined by out pets, right? Well post 50 mages have to scrounge abound looking for PET spells! The same with pre 50 levels, we had to research over half our pets. Now this would not have been so bad if the research words weren't ultra rare drops from dungeon MOBS!!! (I hear Verant has fixed this to some degree)<P>Mages have NO mana generating capabilities, nor not ONE personal shield that will hold off an angry mob till you can get that spell off (no absorbing shields). No spell that will allow you to escape, other than gate (which every pure caster has). It took 6 MONTHS before Verant realized that it was WRONG about our pets dual wielding, and THEN to fix it, they NERFED all other pets in regards to hast bounus for weapons (THAT made mages VERY popular <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/rolleyes.gif"> )<P>While Verant has jumped to make other classes 'group friendly' they still insist that our summoning of 'trinkets' is what a full group REALLY wants! LOL!
